name: Jenniffer González

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: On January 28, 2021, I introduced HR537, the Supplemental Security Act, to extend the SSI program to the territories. The vulnerable Americans living in the territories are no less deserving of our help than those vulnerable Americans living in the States and DC.

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: The exclusion of the Americans living in 🇵🇷 from the SSI program, and other federal entitlement programs, is unfair and unjustified, which hurts the most vulnerable of our citizens that we, as a nation, are called to protect.

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: Today we remember them and all others who gave all for us, and commit ourselves once again to never forget, and to continue honoring their memory by defending freedom and justice everywhere.

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: For more than a century, men and women from Puerto Rico have served in the US Military. Over two thousand of them fell on duty, returning home covered in the flag under which they fought, that flag that is missing the star from their own island.

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: Today we remember those who gave the ultimate sacrifice, those who were not able to see the fruit of their struggles, who did not return to homes and families and futures, so that we could harvest those fruits, and live free in our home and family and have a future.

name: Jenniffer González
tweet_text: On this day, across our nation, we pause to remember and honor a special group. We commemorate the fallen who gave their lives in the military service of the United States, keeping their oath to protect it, standing for freedom. #MemorialDay2020 https://t.co/bJuJGb3eHU
